# Local config for the knowledge-tools CLI (the daemon + the compile/synthesize/resolve jobs).
# Copy to .env (gitignored) and set the values. Values are literal — use absolute paths,
# not ~ or $HOME. An explicit env var (or the daemon unit's Environment=) overrides what's set here.
#
# This is separate from mcp/.env, which configures the MCP server.
#
# Scheduler: `knowledge-tools install` registers one daemon per vault (a systemd user service on
# Linux, a launchd LaunchAgent on macOS) that owns scheduling internally — same cron knobs below on
# both OSes (a CRON_TZ= prefix picks the timezone). On macOS the daemon (a LaunchAgent) only runs
# while you're logged in (no linger equivalent), so a night job needs the Mac on and logged in.

# REQUIRED. Absolute path to the vault repo (inbox watched + compiled, wiki written).
KNOWLEDGE_REPO=/path/to/vault

# Optional. The instance name for this vault — one daemon per instance. Default 'default' (a
# single-vault host needs nothing here). To run SEVERAL vaults on one host, run
# `knowledge-tools install` once per vault with a distinct KNOWLEDGE_INSTANCE + KNOWLEDGE_REPO; each
# gets its own daemon, lock, schedule, and config file at ~/.config/knowledge-tools/<instance>.env
# (install writes it). Different vaults run concurrently; the three jobs within a vault serialize.
# KNOWLEDGE_INSTANCE=default
#   e.g.  KNOWLEDGE_INSTANCE=work KNOWLEDGE_REPO=/path/to/work-vault knowledge-tools install

# Optional. Path to the claude binary the vault jobs invoke (default ~/.local/bin/claude).
# CLAUDE_BIN=/home/you/.local/bin/claude

# Optional. Seconds between allowed manual compiles (default 3600).
# KNOWLEDGE_COMPILE_COOLDOWN=3600

# Optional. Scheduled-compile cadence — a cron expression (default @hourly). Re-run
# `knowledge-tools install` after changing. The worker no-ops cheaply on an empty inbox, so a
# frequent cadence only does real work when there are captures. Examples:
# @hourly | @daily | 0 * * * * | */30 * * * * (every 30 min).
# KNOWLEDGE_COMPILE_SCHEDULE=@hourly

# Optional. Synthesis cadence — the heavy whole-corpus /synthesize pass that reconciles drift
# and OPENS judgment calls. Keep it rare. Default 'CRON_TZ=America/Detroit 30 4 * * 0'
# (weekly Sunday ~4:30am local) to land on off-peak Claude Max capacity. The CRON_TZ= prefix
# picks the timezone. Re-run `knowledge-tools install` after changing.
# KNOWLEDGE_SYNTHESIZE_SCHEDULE=CRON_TZ=America/Detroit 30 4 * * 0

# Optional. Resolve cadence — the light /resolve pass that applies your answers to open calls
# and CLOSES them. Short-circuits cheaply when nothing is answered. Default
# 'CRON_TZ=America/Detroit 30 3 * * *' (daily ~3:30am local), staggered an hour before synthesize
# so they don't collide on the shared lock. Re-run `knowledge-tools install` after changing.
# KNOWLEDGE_RESOLVE_SCHEDULE=CRON_TZ=America/Detroit 30 3 * * *

# Optional. Which channel carries synthesize's judgment calls — 'github' or 'files'.
#   github — calls are GitHub issues (vault:judgment-call / vault:needs-verification, answered
#            by adding the vault:answered label). Needs git + a GitHub remote + an authed gh.
#   files  — calls are files in inbox/.review/, answered from chat via the MCP connector. No
#            git, no GitHub, no gh — works on a bare folder synced by Dropbox/Syncthing.
# Unset = auto-detect: 'github' only if gh is authed AND an origin remote exists, else 'files'.
# KNOWLEDGE_REVIEW_CHANNEL=files

# gh auth (only for the 'github' review channel, never for compile): in that channel
# synthesize/resolve run `gh issue ...` from inside their Claude run, so the host needs the
# GitHub CLI installed, on PATH, and authenticated — `gh auth login` once (stored in
# ~/.config/gh). The 'files' channel and compile never call gh.

# --- Static site (optional) — scripts/vault-site.sh builds the Quartz render the service serves
# at / (see service/README.md "Static website"). Run it on the host (needs Node >= 20); it reads
# only index.md + wiki/ and publishes OUTSIDE the vault. All knobs below are optional.
# Where the built site is published — bind-mount THIS into the container at /site (read-only).
# Default ~/.local/state/knowledge-tools/site/<instance>.
# KNOWLEDGE_SITE_ROOT=/home/you/.local/state/knowledge-tools/site/default
# Public host for absolute URLs in RSS/sitemap (navigation is relative, so this is cosmetic);
# set it to your real host. WITHOUT scheme. Default example.com.
# KNOWLEDGE_SITE_BASE_URL=knowledge.example.com
# Site page title (default "Knowledge Vault").
# KNOWLEDGE_SITE_TITLE=Knowledge Vault
# Pinned Quartz version — a git checkout, not an npm dep (default v4.5.2). v5 is a port, not a bump.
# KNOWLEDGE_QUARTZ_REF=v4.5.2
# Prune vault-site build logs older than N days (default 30).
# KNOWLEDGE_SITE_LOG_RETENTION_DAYS=30

# Optional. Path to the lockfile this vault's three jobs (compile/synthesize/resolve) acquire so
# they never run concurrently. Defaults to ~/.local/state/knowledge-tools/vault-<instance>.lock —
# keyed by KNOWLEDGE_INSTANCE so different vaults get different locks and run concurrently. Only
# override if you must point it elsewhere.
# KNOWLEDGE_VAULT_LOCK=/home/you/.local/state/knowledge-tools/vault-default.lock
